If you make changes to a shader file you can reload the graphics without exiting Elite by adding the following code to end of your d3dx.ini

;------------Start-----------------------
[Hunting]
hunting=1
reload_fixes = no_modifiers VK_F11
reload_config = no_modifiers VK_F11
toggle_hunting = no_modifiers VK_DECIMAL
show_original = no_modifiers VK_F9
;------------End-------------------------


Key bindings:

F11 - reloads the shaders and ini (show changes you make)
F9 - show the unmodded (orange) HUD
NUMPAD DECIMAL - hide 3Dmigoto developer mode (improves FPS)

 * you can change any of these key bindings
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/inputdev/virtual-key-codes
